    • uiReadyGeneral

      public static ActivityBuilder uiReadyGeneral()
      Creates a new activity builder for a ui ready "general" activity. The following fields will be set on the activity:
      • Claim: If a claim is provided either explicitly via onClaim or implicitly, by calling this method as an argument to the ClaimBuilder withActivity method, then the specified claim will be used. Otherwise a new UI ready auto claim will be created.
      • Activity pattern will be set to the activity pattern with the code "general_reminder"
      • Target date will be now plus one day
      • Escalation date will be now plus one day
      • Subject will be set to a unique string of the form "SubjectN" where N is an integer
      • Priority will be set to Normal
      • The activity will be assigned to the same user and group as the claim
      Returns:
      the new builder

    • uiReadyGeneral

      public static ActivityBuilder uiReadyGeneral(Claim claim)
      Creates a new activity builder for a ui ready "general" activity on the given claim. The following fields will be set:
      • Target date will be now plus one day
      • Escalation date will be now plus one day
      • Activity pattern will be set to the activity pattern with the code "general_reminder"
      • Subject will be set to a unique string of the form "SubjectN" where N is an integer
      • The activity will be assigned to the same user and group as the claim
      Parameters:
      claim - the claim on which the activity will be created
      Returns:
      the new builder

    • uiReadyGeneral

      public static ActivityBuilder uiReadyGeneral(ValueGenerator<? extends Claim> claimBuilder)
      Creates a new activity builder for a ui ready "general" activity on the claim returned by the given value generator. If the claim value generator is null a new ui ready auto claim will be generated. The following fields will be set on the activity:
      • Target date will be now plus one day
      • Escalation date will be now plus one day
      • Activity pattern will be set to the activity pattern with the code "general_reminder"
      • Subject will be set to a unique string of the form "SubjectN" where N is an integer
      • The activity will be assigned to the same user and group as the claim
      Parameters:
      claimBuilder - a value generator that will return the claim on which the activity will be created, or null
      Returns:
      the new builder

    • withActivityPatternByCode

      public ActivityBuilder withActivityPatternByCode(String activityPatternCode)
      Sets the activity's pattern to the pattern with the given code. The pattern must already exist in the database; typically this means it should be one of the standard activity patterns in the system data.
      Parameters:
      activityPatternCode - the code of the desired activity pattern
      Returns:
      the modified builder
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if there is no pattern with the given code

    • assignedTo

      public ActivityBuilder assignedTo(String userName)
      Sets the activity's assigned user, group and assignment status by looking up an existing user then setting the assigned user to that user, the assigned group to the user's group and the assignment status to "assigned". If the user is in multiple groups then the groups are sorted alphabetically by name and the first group is used.
      Parameters:
      userName - the name of the desired assigned user
      Returns:
      the modified builder

    • withSameAssignmentAs

      public ActivityBuilder withSameAssignmentAs(Assignable assignable)

      Parameters:
      assignable - the object from which to copy the assigned user, group and status fields
      Returns:
      the modified builder

    • assignedToClaimOwner

      public ActivityBuilder assignedToClaimOwner()
      Sets the activity's assigned user, group and assignment status to the same values as those found on the activity's claim. If the activity's claim is not set by a call to onClaim before this method is called then an IllegalStateException will be thrown when the builder's create method is called
      Returns:
      the modified builder
